# Design Decision Log (Adaptive Risk Reduction)

ARR means **Adaptive Risk Reduction** (not maintenance-only). The suite spans workforce, training, assets, dispatch, supply, and compliance authority.

## V1 and ownership

- Every product ships in V1 with a **real API, worker, database, and UI** — no domain absorption into another product’s schema or service.
- **NexArr**: control plane — login, tenants, entitlement, licensing, launch, service authority.
- **StaffArr**: workforce backbone — who someone is, org, permissions, readiness.
- **Compliance Core**: authority layer — vocabulary, keys, mappings, rule context (not product workflows).

## Data and integration

- **Separate PostgreSQL per product**; no cross-product foreign keys.
- Connect products via **APIs and events**, plus local mirror/reference tables — never DB constraints across services.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — cross-product FK
model.WorkOrder { public int SupplyArrPartId { get; set; } } // FK to SupplyArr DB

// ✅ GOOD — local mirror + API/event
model.WorkOrderPartLine {
  public string SourceProduct { get; set; } = "SupplyArr";
  public Guid SourcePartId { get; set; }
  public DateTimeOffset SourceUpdatedAt { get; set; }
}
```

## Stack

- **Render first**: static sites, web services, workers, PostgreSQL, Redis-compatible Key Value; define in `render.yaml`.
- **Docker** for .NET 10 APIs and workers.
- **React + Vite** for suite shell, product UIs, marketing site.
- **Lucide React** for icons (stroke set, consistent imports).

## Product boundary decisions

| Area | Owner | Do not |
|------|--------|--------|
| Procurement (vendors, PR/PO, receiving, inventory, pricing, lead times) | SupplyArr | Put in MaintainArr |
| Driver as a person; qualification/readiness | StaffArr (+ TrainArr for training proof) | Treat as RoutArr-owned identity |
| Training proof, completions, recertification | TrainArr → publish to StaffArr | Duplicate readiness truth in TrainArr |
| Operational workflow and decisions | Each product API | Replace with Compliance Core workflows |

Compliance Core supplies **rule context and results**; products own **facts, workflow actions, and overrides** (with permission + audit).
